# Example per-chassis env template — the CATALOG of runtime env var NAMES an
# Agent Keep chassis may require. Re-namespaced from the Foundry's
# agent.env.template.example (ADR 0001 transplant). Which of these a given chassis
# needs is decided by its SPEC: a component only reads its env var when the spec
# selects that component.
#
# DOC-ONLY. This file changes NO deploy behavior and touches NO systemd unit. Copy
# the relevant lines into /etc/agent-keep/<slug>.env (root-owned, mode 0600 — see
# .verity/deploy-access.md) and fill VALUES on the server.
#
# RULE: variable NAMES only, here and in git. Every VALUE is deploy-time only and
# NEVER lives in git, in a spec, or baked into an image. A component that needs
# its var and does not find it fails loudly at boot, naming the var.

# --- Digest-pinned image refs (written by deploy.sh) -----------------------
# The paired chassis runs three images; deploy.sh pins each to an immutable digest.
WORKER_IMAGE_REF=
PROXY_IMAGE_REF=
MECHANIC_IMAGE_REF=
WORKER_IMAGE_DIGEST=
MECHANIC_IMAGE_DIGEST=

# --- Host bind interface + per-surface ports -------------------------------
BIND_HOST=
WORKER_BIND_PORT=
MECHANIC_BIND_PORT=

# --- Persistence: sqlite tier ----------------------------------------------
# Required when a spec selects persistence.tier: sqlite (the default-chatbot and
# the mechanic both do). Component: agent_runtime sqlite_persistence.
SQLITE_PATH=

# --- Persistence: postgres tier --------------------------------------------
# Required when a spec selects persistence.tier: postgres.
# Component: agent_runtime postgres_persistence / pgvector_memory / retrieval_history.
POSTGRES_DSN=

# --- Gateway queue: redis --------------------------------------------------
# Required when a spec selects gateway.queue: redis. Component: redis_queue.
REDIS_URL=

# --- Model provider: anthropic ---------------------------------------------
# Required when a spec declares models.anthropic (the live worker variant,
# specs/default-chatbot.live.yaml). The NAME is spec-declared via
# models.anthropic.apiKeyEnv; ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is the schema default.
# Component: agent_runtime anthropic_provider.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# --- Egress proxy tuning (OPTIONAL; empty => default, issue #13) ------------
# The proxy reads its allowlist from the mounted spec.yaml (KEEP_SPEC_PATH); these
# only override its listen interface/port, audit path, and ingress-hardening caps.
# The unit pins KEEP_EGRESS_HOST to `egress-proxy` (internal-net alias) so the
# control port binds the internal interface only (issue #11); this value is
# informational. HEAD_TIMEOUT_SECONDS (10) / MAX_CONNECTIONS (256) bound
# slowloris / half-open floods. Component: keep_egress.
KEEP_EGRESS_HOST=
KEEP_EGRESS_PORT=
KEEP_EGRESS_AUDIT_PATH=
KEEP_EGRESS_HEAD_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=
KEEP_EGRESS_MAX_CONNECTIONS=

# --- The Mechanic: worker bundle directory ---------------------------------
# The mechanic reads the paired worker's bundle (spec + audit log) read-only. The
# systemd unit sets MECHANIC_WORKER_DIR=/srv/worker-bundle inline (deploy-config,
# never in the spec — contract log-egress); listed here for completeness.
MECHANIC_WORKER_DIR=

# --- Channel: webex / slack (post-skeleton stages) -------------------------
# Required when a spec selects a webex/slack channel (ADR 0003: dev-http first;
# platform channels are later stages). NAMES only.
WEBEX_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
WEBEX_BOT_TOKEN=
SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET=
SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=

# --- MCP tool grants (per-agent, spec-declared) ----------------------------
# MCP tool grants declare their OWN secret env NAMES per spec, via each grant's
# verification/secretEnvs. Add whichever your spec names here; the same NAME-only,
# value-at-deploy-time rule applies.
